olive oil
1 packet brown rice
1 potato
1 carrot
2 clove garlic
1 bag baby broccoli
20 g butter
1 sachet Mild North Indian Spice Blend
1 sachet Mumbai Spice Blend
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
1 packet coconut milk
¼ cup water
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet Crushed Roasted Cashews

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Half-fill a medium saucepan with water.
Add brown rice and a generous pinch of salt.
• Bring to the boil over high heat and cook,
uncovered, until tender, 25-30 minutes.
• Drain the rice and return to saucepan.

• Meanwhile, cut potato and carrot into bite-sized
chunks.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Drizzle
generously with olive oil and season with salt
and pepper.
• Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then roast until
tender, 20-25 minutes.

• When the veggies have 15 minutes remaining,
finely chop garlic. Cut baby broccoli into thirds.

• In a large frying pan, heat the butter with a
drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
Cook baby broccoli until softened, 5-6 minutes.
• Add garlic, mild North Indian spice blend and
Mumbai spice blend and cook until fragrant,
1 minute.

• Add vegetable stock powder, coconut milk and
the water to the pan. Simmer until thickened,
2-4 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, then stir through
roasted veggies and baby spinach leaves until
wilted. Season to taste.

• Divide brown rice between plates. Top with
hearty potato and coconut curry.
• Garnish with crushed roasted cashews to serve.
Enjoy!